    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reintroduce the Health and Social Care Levy",
        "additional_details": "The gross inadequacies of the social care system have been a running sore for decades, a problem which both major parties have neglected.\r\n\r\nThe UK's population is ageing, so every year of neglect allows the problems to worsen. At the last General Election a plan to address these problems was promised, and later a funding plan was introduced. But now these provisions have been withdrawn.\r\n\r\nThe UK's NHS has been tested almost to destruction by the Covid pandemic, and needs additional funding to recover.",
        "background": "Reinstate the Government's specific levy to increase funding for health and social care, to address long-standing funding deficits and inadequacies in these sectors, and help them recover following the impact of Covid.",
